Title: 'Shipping' Real People For Profit
Description:
On-screen romance is fun to watch, but what happens when two (attractive) actors are made to milk their chemistry in the public light for all its worth? Bound to the same movies, shows, and even public events… all for companies to exploit their image as an “ideal” romantic couple? 

Let’s dive into the wild world of “Love Teams”, a phenomenon unique to the entertainment industry of the Philippines that make Hollywood “ships” look like child’s play. I explore the dark side of this national trend behind its often pure, wholesome façade: particularly the loyal fans that fight to keep these “couples” together forever. ❤️‍🩹

- 

🕦TIMESTAMPS:🕝 
0:00 – Prologue (Love stories & the rise of “ships”)

17:30 – Wrath of the “AlDub Nation”
21:36 – Loss of artistic individuality
27:29 – So… are love teams bad for the industry?
30:32 – Is the reel-to-real romance dying?
31:32 – Rise of queer love teams

Title: The "Birds Aren't Real" Conspiracy Theory
Description:
Bird watching goes both ways. 🐦👁️

Join me as I dive into the conspiracy theory that’s captured a generation, and its underlying message in the wild west era of internet misinformation. 

"We needed a way to keep an eye on the American citizens without them knowing. It was imperative, for their own safety of course. We hired only the best. It took years. We designed, built, tested, failed. We persisted. Eventually, over decades, we had it. A fleet of covert technological surveillance devices unlike anything the world had ever seen. We called them, 'Birds'." - Richard Nixon, 1978 (from birdsarentreal.com) 

-

Description:

Title: Superhero Fatigue, Martin Scorsese, & the "Marvel Problem"
Description:

Legendary director Martin Scorsese caused quite the social media stir in 2019 with his statements saying Marvel movies aren't “cinema”; or at the very least, are edging out the types of “cinema” he and his fellow directors have valued over the years. Title: The Quest for Social Media “Clout”: A Deep Dive

Welp, algorithm ruined. 💩 The phenomena of “social media fame” has undoubtedly brought plenty of talents, ideas, and movements to light – but how can a lust/fascination for “online clout” corrupt others?

Title: Did "Emo Culture" Promote Depression?

Featuring spoilers for Maleficent (2014), Joker (2019), and Cruella (2021). 💀

Title: Our Love for Fictional Characters (& Toxic Fan Entitlement)
Description:
Lethal drinking game: take a shot every time I say “parasocial relationship” 🍸

Ever cry when your favourite TV characters die? When your ship doesn’t make it? When a long-running TV show you’ve invested hours of your life into ends in a hot-garbage finale? Yeah it’s a mood. 🙃

I dive into these strong bonds we make with fiction, why they happen, and the worst (and best) sides of them. 👥
